4623	    AlgebraicGeometry.appIso_inv_res_assoc}
4624	  \uses{lem:tile_section_ring_identity}
4625	  The general-open companion of Lemma~\ref{lem:tile_section_ring_identity}. For an \emph{arbitrary}
4626	  open \(V \subseteq \Spec R_g\), the restriction to the iterated-image open \(\iota(V)\) of the
4627	  global-sections identification \(\theta_R\) of \(\Spec R\) equals the localisation map followed by the
4628	  global-sections identification of \(\Spec R_g\), the restriction to \(V\), and the two (inverse)
4629	  open-immersion section isomorphisms of the tile read at \(V\):
4630	  \[
4631	    \rho^{\iota(V)} \circ \theta_R
4632	    \;=\;
4633	    \beta_{\hookrightarrow,V}^{-1} \circ \beta_{\mathrm{aff},V}^{-1} \circ \rho^{V}_{R_g} \circ \theta_{R_g} \circ \lambda.
4634	  \]
4635	  This supplies the ring identity at the target open \(V = D(\bar f)\) consumed by the general-open
4636	  scalar reconciliation Lemma~\ref{lem:tile_scalar_compat_genV}. (The two section-restriction naturality
4637	  wrappers \texttt{appIso\_inv\_res} and \texttt{appIso\_inv\_res\_assoc} used in the proof are bundled
4638	  into this block.)
4639	\end{lemma}
4640	\begin{proof}
4641	  \uses{lem:tile_section_ring_identity}
4642	  Derive from the \(V = \top\) case (Lemma~\ref{lem:tile_section_ring_identity}) by post-composing both
4643	  sides with the structure-sheaf restriction \(\iota(V) \le \iota(\top)\) and pushing that restriction
4644	  through the two open-immersion section isomorphisms. The push-through is the section-restriction form
4645	  of the open-immersion section-iso naturality: for an open immersion \(f\) and opens \(U' \le U\), the
4646	  inverse section iso at \(U\) followed by the \(Y\)-restriction \(f(U') \le f(U)\) equals the
4647	  \(X\)-restriction \(U' \le U\) followed by the inverse section iso at \(U'\) (restated with explicit
4648	  \(\hom\)-of-\(\le\) restrictions and image opens as the wrappers \texttt{appIso\_inv\_res} and its
4649	  associativity-folded variant \texttt{appIso\_inv\_res\_assoc} so it rewrites cleanly inside the
4650	  composite, with explicit order-restriction maps and image opens). The residual restriction
4651	  \(\rho^{\top}_{R_g}\) on \(\Spec R_g\) is the identity by
4652	  uniqueness of morphisms in the thin category of opens.
4653	\end{proof}
